message.content: with something of a start I remembered the man who'd brought us into this business. "Maybe you don't know about Appleton, Dan?" "Know what?" "That he's dead," I said. I watched him because I was always fascinated by the way he looked when you tried to surprise him. "Dead?" he said. "Yes. Dead. Snuffed out of the clock. Picked off with a shotgun outside the Palace last night."
